{
  "text": "Hence k is an accelerant on [−T, T] whenever T < π 2 . Furthermore, again using the formulas from [CITATION_1] , one computes that for each τ < π 2 the resolvent kernel associated to k, that is, the solution γ τ (t, s) of (1.2), is given by",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "123446769"
